## Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Next.js App Router project following the latest official documentation.

### Changes Made

**1. Package Installation**
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` package (version 1.1.0)
- Updated package.json to include the new dependency
- Generated updated package-lock.json

**2. Configuration**
Modified: `src/app/layout.tsx`
- Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/next';`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component to the root layout body
- Positioned after the existing `<Analytics />` component for consistency

### Implementation Details

The configuration follows the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router projects:
- Used the framework-specific import from `@vercel/speed-insights/next`
- Placed the component in the root layout to track performance across all pages
- Maintained the existing code structure and styling

### Build Verification

✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ All routes generated correctly (32 total routes)
✅ No TypeScript compilation errors
✅ Component properly integrated alongside existing Analytics

### Next Steps

To enable Speed Insights on Vercel:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Navigate to the Speed Insights section in your Vercel dashboard
3. Click "Enable" to activate Speed Insights
4. After users visit your site, performance metrics will appear in the dashboard within a few days

The Speed Insights tracking will automatically be available at `/_vercel/speed-insights/*` routes after deployment.
